The paper deals with the task of wikifying scientific abstracts, which involves mention extraction and entity linking. This task is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of Wikipedia as a rich repository of concepts also suggests a connection to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information systems (cs.SI). Finally, the use of citation and author publication networks for entity linking suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB).
